GIT Commands learned

git init //making a directory gitable

1. git add   //to add a new file to staging area/put a modified tracked file in staging area

2. git commit //commit changes

3. git status //checking which files are in modified region

4. git diff //diff files from unstaged and staged

5. git commit -a // directly commit trackable files


6. git commit --amend //changing the last commit we made

7. git log //getting a log of all commitmenets

8. git log -p //getting the diffs in each commit

9. gitk //graphical user interface

10. git remote add origin [url]
	git remote -v
	git push origin master
	